ild as they wish. Teachers don't have a right to be bad. &#10;I didn't home school my kids but I did take them out of a local failing school and send them to a religious school which has an ethos of 25% exam mark as unacceptable. I also pay for extra tuition after school, something that I really can't afford but I have chosen to do and go without holidays abroad. &#10;I can only go by this article. CiF posts are all throw away comments!!!!"/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="734" language="en" documentId="805" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="PaulMetcalf01" date="07 January 2011 1:58pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/9053007" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="3" thumbsDown="0" origId="805" notes="" title="Why I home school my children"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="10"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="11" end="229"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="230" end="356"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="357" end="661"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="662" end="734"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55"/></xmi:XMI>